  "response": "Here are some substitutes for parsnips in recipes:\n\n1. Carrots\n- Similar texture and sweetness\n- Good in roasted dishes and soups\n\n2. Turnips\n- Similar root vegetable consistency\n- Slightly less sweet, but good in stews and roasts\n\n3. Potatoes\n- Similar starchy texture\n- Best for mashing or roasting\n\n4. Rutabagas\n- Similar root vegetable flavor\n- Good in soups and roasted dishes\n\n5. Sweet potatoes\n- Similar sweetness and texture\n- Great for roasting and mashing\n\n6. Celery root\n- Similar earthy flavor\n- Works well in soups and pur\u00e9es\n\n7. White carrots\n- Most similar in appearance and flavor\n- Good direct replacement\n\n8. Kohlrabi\n- Similar texture when cooked\n- Works in roasted and mashed dishes\n\nWhen substituting, consider the specific recipe and desired flavor profile. Some substitutes work better in certain dishes than others. The closest replacements are typically other root vegetables with similar textures and mild, sweet flavors.",
